ru.ifmo.ctddev.maltsev.implementor

Class Implementor

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.ifmo.ctddev.maltsev.implementor.Implementor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.Impler

    public class Implementor
extends Object
implements info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.Impler
    The Implementor class implements Impler interface.

    Class gives instruments for generating compilable representation of java Class. With method implement can be generated stub of Class that can be compiled without errors. All other methods are needed for supporting it.

    See Also:
    Impler

      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
        Generates code of class implementing an interface or a class specified by given token

        Created class has name same to the name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name.

        Specified by:
        implement in interface info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.Impler
        Parameters:
        token - - type token to create implementation for
        root - - root directory
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

      • printMethods

        private void printMethods(Class<?> c,
                          Set<String> methodSet)
                   throws IOException
        Generates string representation for each unimplemented method of implemented (or extended) Class.

        This method generates totally completed block of code of stubs for unimplemented methods in interface or abstract class. To prevent double-implementation should be given an Set with signatures (That are generated in writeSignature) of Methods witch is already done.

        The result of this method will be written in writer

        Parameters:
        c - - type token of Class methods of which should be implemented
        methodSet - - set of signatures of methods that are already written
        Throws:
        IOException - .

      • writeMethod

        private String writeMethod(Method m)
        Generates string representation of given Method.

        The result is: [modifiers] [return type] [method name] ([arguments]) ['throws' declaration] { return [value]; }

        Parameters:
        m - - given Method witch should be implemented
        Returns:
        String representation of given Method

      • writeType

        private String writeType(Class<?> type)
        Generates string representation of given type.

        If it is a raw type then will be returned string with the same name, but if it is an array then will be added "[]" for each dimension

        Parameters:
        type - - type-token of representing Class
        Returns:

      • writeExceptions

        private String writeExceptions(Class<?>[] types)
        Generates string of given declared method's exceptions.

        If method has declared exceptions then will be returned string of format: throws [Exceptions names,]... If method has more than one declared exception then they will be separated with ',' char.

        Parameters:
        types - - array of possible exceptions for such method
        Returns:
        String that declares all possible exceptions
